The defendant Clinton Edmond Benion was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Cocaine (2nd+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Defendant Clinton Edmond Benion in court with attorney Mark Allan Dluzak.  Nicholas Steven Cerwin appeared for David Behm for the State of Wisconsin.   Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.
AS TO BOTH COUNTS:  
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, credit for 5 days, Huber privileges for work, work crew, AODA treatment, child care, school. IMPOSED and STAYED. The Court placed the defendant on probation for a period of 18 months.   Court approved participation in the Dosage Probation Pilot Program and probation may be terminated early if the defendant successfully completes the program and all other conditions of probation.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-Serve 10 days condition time in the House of Corrections with Huber release for work. Court stayed the sentence and ordered a report date of 8/3/15 to the House of Corrections.
-No violations of State or Federal law that rise to the level of probable cause
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens
-Work or school
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification course
-Successfully complete a parenting course
-6 month drivers license suspension
-Court costs and victim/witness surcharges are to be paid by 1/30/17; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay related surcharge by 1/30/17; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Court imposed and stayed condition time of 30 days straight time to be imposed at the discretion of the agent
